HEADWORD: Incurrence
<hw>In*cur"rence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Incur</er>.]</ety> <def>The act of incurring, bringing on, or
subjecting one's self to (something troublesome or burdensome); <as>as,
the <ex>incurrence</ex> of guilt, debt, responsibility,
etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incurrent</ent>⟦br⟧
